asthma.name: Percent of People Diagnosed with Asthma
asthma.description: Percent of people that responded yes to "Has a doctor or other health professional ever told you that you have asthma?"

binge_drinker.name: Percent of People that have a Binge Drinking Episode
binge_drinker.description: Percent of people that report at least one binge drking episode in the last year. Binge drinking is defined as having more than 5 drinks on a single occasion for men and 4 drinks on a single occasion for women. The SHOW survey asks how many days in the past year the respondent had 5 or more drinks.

count_walk_to.name: Average Number of Amenities within Walking Distance
count_walk_to.description: SHOW asks respondents to rate a list of 18 amenities (e.g. parks, supermarkets, post office) on the amount of time it would take to walk to it. This is a count of the number of amenities that the respondents said they could walk to in under 5 minutes.

current_smoker.name: Percent of People who Currently Smoke
current_smoker.description: Percent of people that answered yes to the question, "Do you smoke cigarettes now?"

dozing_off.name: Percent of People with High Chance of Dozing Off
dozing_off.description: SHOW asks if people would be likely to doze off while doing one of 8 activities (e.g. watching TV, riding in a car). This is the percent of people that reported a high chance of dozing off in at least one situation.

flu_shot.name: Percent of People that received Annual Flu Vaccine
flu_shot.description: Percent of people that reported they had a flu shot in the last 12 months.

fruit_veg_access.name: Percent of People with Access to Fruits and Veggies
fruit_veg_access.description: Percent of people that agree or strongly agree with the statemetn, "I have easy access to fruits and vegetables in my community."

fruit_veg_eating.name: Average Fruits and Vegetables Consumed Per Day
fruit_veg_eating.description: SHOW asks respondents for various information about their normal eating habits. Based on their answers an average number of fruits and veggies per day is computed based on standard methods.

heavy_drinker.name: Percent of People that are Heavy Drinkers
heavy_drinker.description: Respondents are asked how much wine, beer, and liquor they drink in a normal week. Heavy drinkers are defined by the CDC as men that have more than 15 drinks per week and women that have more than 8 drinks per week.

hypertension.name: Percent of People With Hypertension
hypertension.description: SHOW measures blood pressure for all respondents. People are considered hypertensive if they have BP over 140/90. If a respondent reports they are currently being treated with anti-hypertensive medication they are also considered to have hypertension.

indoor_smoke.name: Percent of People Exposed to Smoke in their Homes
indoor_smoke.description: Percent of people that report that they or someone they live with smokes in their home.

life_events.name: Average Number of Life Changes for Each Person
life_events.description: SHOW asks respondents if they have experienced any of a list of 43 life changes (e.g. divorce, moving, changing jobs, change in eating habits). This is the average count of the life changes in the past year.

overweight.name: Percent of People Overweight
overweight.description: SHOW measures people's height and weight. From this we calculate their body mass index (BMI). A BMI over 25 is considered overweight.

pack_years.name: Average Pack Years among Current or Former Smokers
pack_years.description: Calculated for people that have ever smoked. It is equivalnt to smoking 1 pack per day for 1 year.

poor_oral_health.name: Percent of People Reporting Poor Oral Health
poor_oral_health.description: If respondents reported the condition of their teeth was "fair" or "poor", they are counted in the percent of people reporting poor oral health.

sleep_hours.name: Average Hours of Sleep
sleep_hours.description: SHOW asks a series of questions about work/school nights and weekend nights for respondents that work. This is the average hours of sleep for all respondents.

total_cholesterol.name: Average Total Cholesterol
total_cholesterol.description: Each respondent that agrees to a blood test is analyzed for total cholesterol by Marshfield Labs.
